Date: Thu 14 Dec 2017
From: Steve Berger <steve@gideononline.com> [edited]


Re: Diphtheria - Bangladesh: fatal, susp, Rohingya refugee camp, ex Myanmar, WHO 20171214.5502309
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Regarding the current outbreak of diphtheria in Bangladesh among Royingya refugees from Myanmar, both countries have experienced strikingly similar disease incidence and vaccination uptake for several decades [1,2]. (see graph at https://www.gideononline.com/2017/12/14/diphtheria-myanmar-bangladesh/)

References:
1. Berger S. Diphtheria: Global Status, 2017.ï¿½347 pages, 447 graphs, 533 references. Gideon e-books, https://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/diphtheria-global-status/
2. Gideon e-Gideon multi-graph tool, https://www.gideononline.com/cases/multi-graphs/

